project-basis: It's a URL provided by domain.com strapped to an HTML and CSS file stored on a github pages page.
project-challenges: Successfully completing any other project but this.
project-future-plans: To take forth the simplistic knowledge gained in completing this task, and to roll forward with this knowledge into the future. Perhaps after this we will complete something slightly bigger, and then we'll move on to complete something just a little bit bigger than even that, and even though all these things in the short term will appear to be very small, perhaps some day far in the future we will look back at them and realize just how far we've actually managed to go and just how much we really did manage to bring ourselves to achieve.
project-purpose: It serves as a reminder and an inspiration to never be afraid of failure and the necessity to sometimes take small steps and make use of perseverance to achieve a greater goal.
project-inspiration: After achieving nothing for 30 straight hours, we wanted to prove our ability to complete at least one thing at a hackathon.
project-lessons-learned: Sometimes it's better just to achieve
project-subtitle: After 30 hours of nothing, we wanted to achieve at least one thing.
